            W<hi rend="smallcaps">ARD</hi>. A<hi rend="smallcaps">SSESSED</hi> N<hi rend="smallcaps">O</hi>. L<hi rend="smallcaps">OCATI</hi></ab>-->        
        <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_nhg.00050.jpg" type="recto"/>
        <div1><head type="sub">"Churches)</head>
        <p><handShift new="#h1"/><del rend="overstrike">In 1690</del> <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear">As early as</add> 1695, Independent
        churches were common on 
        Long Island, acknowledging
        no Presbytery or Episcopate,
        but voluntar<subst><del rend="overwrite" seq="1">y</del><add rend="overwrite" place="over" seq="2">ily</add></subst> coming together,
        and supporting what minister
        suited them.&#8212; <del rend="overstrike">But</del>
        <subst><del rend="overwrite" seq="1">t</del><add rend="overwrite" place="over" seq="2">T</add></subst>he Dutch Reformed and 
        the English Episcopal
        were the main sects&#8212;
        but <subst><del rend="overstrike" seq="1">in</del> <add rend="unmarked" place="supralinear" seq="2">on</add></subst> New York island
        there were churches of
        French Protestants, and many 
        other orders, including a
        Jews' Synagogue.&#8212; Every 
        faith indeed was represented here.</p></div1>
